Implementation guidance: Update .github/workflows/release.yml by moving the top-level permissions block under jobs.build-and-upload.permissions. The reusable workflow call job should explicitly grant contents: write and packages: write because the called workflow attaches release assets and uploads to GHCR. Remove the top-level permissions block so token permissions are scoped to the single job that needs them.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_access_administration_events.rego, update matching_admin_events so CloudTrail admin events are matched by both admin event name and the current secret_arn. Add local helper predicates/functions that recognize the collector's secret identifier fields in an event, such as top-level secret_arn, request_parameters.secret_id/secret_arn, requestParameters.secretId/secretArn, or resources entries with ARN/arn equal to secret_arn. Then build matching_admin_events only from events where admin_event_names contains event_name and the event references secret_arn. Keep matching_admin_event_times based on matching_admin_events. Add a regression test in policies/secretsmanager_access_administration_events_test.rego with an admin event for a different secret that must not satisfy the current secret's audit evidence or drive stale/unattributable/missing-timestamp findings.
Implementation guidance: Replace the risk_templates object in policies/secretsmanager_admin_principal_present.rego so it describes admin_principal_missing, not excessive resource-policy access. Use a name/title about a missing administrative principal, a statement explaining that no approved principal has administrative lifecycle rights, CWE-284 or no threat_refs, and remediation tasks such as adding an approved admin principal ARN and documenting required administrative access. Do not change the admin_principal_present or violation logic.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_confidential_disposal_record.rego, change delete_secret_events so it filters DeleteSecret CloudTrail events to only those referencing the current secret_arn. Add a helper for event-to-secret matching that handles likely collector shapes such as top-level secret_arn, request_parameters.secret_id/secret_arn, requestParameters.secretId/secretArn, and resources entries containing ARN/arn. Keep the existing DeleteSecret event_name filter. Add a test in the disposal record test file with DeleteSecret events for another secret and the current secret, proving only the current secret's event affects disposal_authorisation_tag_missing, disposal_event_unattributable, and unrecorded_administration.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_confidential_policy_scope.rego, normalize Principal values locally without introducing a shared package. Add a principal_values(principal_entry)[v] helper that yields the string principal, string principal.AWS, and every string element of principal.AWS when it is an array. Rewrite principal_is_wildcard to check principal_values for '*', rewrite principal_arn to yield each principal_values entry, and leave principal_account_id consuming principal_arn so bare 12-digit accounts and ARN account IDs still work. Add tests for {"AWS": ["*"]} triggering wildcard_principal and {"AWS": [cross-account ARN or bare account]} triggering cross_account_principal/principal_outside_cleared_role_set as applicable.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_confidential_rotation_required.rego, include schedule_expression when evaluating rotation_cadence_too_long. Add schedule_expression parsing consistent with policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego: lower/trim the expression, parse rate(N day/days) into schedule_rate_days, define effective_rotation_days as positive automatically_after_days when present otherwise positive schedule_rate_days, and compare effective_rotation_days to data.max_confidential_rotation_days. If schedule_expression is present but unsupported and automatically_after_days is null or non-positive, add an explicit skip_reason rather than silently passing. Keep not is_service_linked on rotation_cadence_too_long. Add tests for schedule-only rate above the max triggering the violation and schedule-only rate within the max passing.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_owner_tag_present_test.rego, update test_case_insensitive_key_passes so the replacement tags use an Owner key case variant, for example {"oWnEr": "platform"}, instead of {"team": "platform"}. Keep the assertion count(policy.violation) == 0 with input as inp. This should specifically exercise case-insensitive owner-key matching.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture.rego, scope vendor/subprocessor-specific checks to vendor PI secrets. Add an in_scope helper requiring resource_type == "secret", is_pi_secret, and is_vendor_secret. Add a skip_reason for resource_type == "secret", is_pi_secret, and not is_vendor_secret explaining the policy applies only to vendor PI subprocessors. Replace guards on vendor_id_tag_missing, aws_managed_default_kms_key, rotation_disabled, rotation_overdue, principal_wildcard, vendor_integration_role_not_documented, principal_outside_integration_role_set, and excess_actions with in_scope where appropriate. Preserve the existing service-linked exception only on rotation_disabled and rotation_overdue; do not skip KMS or resource-policy posture for service-linked vendor PI secrets. Ensure IntegrationType=vendor with missing VendorId remains in scope so vendor_id_tag_missing still fires.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_privacy_transfer_governance.rego, extend principal_arn to handle Principal.AWS arrays. Add a local principal_values helper or an additional principal_arn rule that, when principal is an object and AWS is an array, iterates each string element and yields it as an ARN/principal value. Ensure principal_account_id continues to handle both bare 12-digit account IDs and ARN-shaped values emitted from the array. Add a regression test with Principal {"AWS": ["arn:aws:iam::999999999999:role/x"]} proving cross_border_principal_undocumented evaluates for array entries.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_resource_policy_least_privilege.rego, normalize principal values locally and support Principal.AWS arrays. Add principal_values(principal_entry)[v] for string principal, string principal.AWS, and each string in principal.AWS arrays. Rewrite principal_is_wildcard to succeed when any normalized value is '*'. Rewrite principal_arn to yield each normalized value, and keep principal_account_id extracting either bare 12-digit accounts or account IDs from ARN values. Preserve allow_effect so Deny statements do not create findings. Add tests for an Allow principal with {"AWS": ["*"]} producing wildcard_principal and an Allow principal with {"AWS": ["999999999999"]} or a cross-account ARN producing cross_account_principal_undocumented.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_rotation_configured_test.rego, strengthen test_service_linked_skipped by asserting policy.skip_reason in addition to count(policy.violation) == 0. Prefer checking the skip_reason string contains or equals the expected service-linked message for owning_service rds.amazonaws.com, matching the policy's actual skip_reason text. Do not change the policy logic.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_rotation_timeliness.rego, add an explicit skip_reason for enabled, non-service-linked secrets with last_rotated_date set but no usable cadence. The new skip should fire when resource_type == "secret", rotation_enabled, not is_service_linked, last_rotated_date != "", not automatically_after_days_positive, schedule_expression == "", and not schedule_rate_days_positive, with a message telling the collector to provide automatically_after_days or a supported schedule_expression. Keep the existing unsupported non-empty schedule_expression skip and rotation_overdue logic unchanged. Add a regression test showing this missing-cadence case returns skip_reason and no rotation_overdue.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_rotation.rego, add rotation_enabled to the vendor_rotation_stale violation conditions, matching vendor_rotation_never_executed. Keep resource_type == "secret", is_vendor_secret, not is_service_linked, not allowed_unrotated_vendor, last_rotated_date != "", and the days_since_rotation threshold. Add or update a test so a vendor secret with rotation_enabled false and an old last_rotated_date does not emit vendor_rotation_stale.
Implementation guidance: In policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_tagging.rego, stop reading data.require_integration_type_tag directly in the integration_type_tag_missing rule. Add a local helper such as require_integration_type_tag := object.get(data, "require_integration_type_tag", true), and use that helper in the violation so a missing data key defaults to enforcement enabled. Add a test that evaluates with data.require_integration_type_tag absent or overridden appropriately and confirms a vendor_id-tagged secret with empty IntegrationType still triggers integration_type_tag_missing.
